'''Santiago Arias Naranjo''' (born 13 January 1992) is a Colombian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]] for [[Argentine Primera División]] club [[Club Atlético Independiente|Independiente]] and the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]].

Arias began his career at [[La Equidad]], before moving to [[Sporting CP]] in Portugal in 2011. In 2013 he signed for Dutch side [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]], where he won three [[Eredivisie]] titles and two [[Johan Cruyff Shield]] trophies, and was named [[Eredivisie Awards|Eredivisie Player of the Year]] for the [[2017–18 Eredivisie|2017–18 season]]. In 2018 he transferred to [[Atlético Madrid]] in Spain, where he won the [[2018 UEFA Super Cup]], later having loan spells at [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] and [[Granada CF|Granada]]. After a stint with [[FC Cincinnati]] in [[Major League Soccer]], where he won the [[Supporters' Shield]] in [[2023 Major League Soccer season|2023]], he joined [[Esporte Clube Bahia|Bahia]] in 2024.

At international level, Arias represented the [[Colombia national under-17 football team|Colombia U17]] and the [[Colombia national under-20 football team|Colombia U20]] before making his senior debut for the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]] in 2013. He has earned over 60 caps and appeared at the [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]] and [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]] editions of the FIFA World Cup, as well as in the [[2015 Copa América|2015]], [[2016 Copa América Centenario|2016]] where Colombia finished third, [[2019 Copa América|2019]], and [[2024 Copa América|2024]] where Colombia finished as runners-up.

== Club career ==
=== La Equidad ===
Arias was a youth product of the [[La Equidad]] academy. He was moved into the senior squad during 2009 making his professional debut that same year against [[Deportes Tolima]]. He soon became a regular for the [[Bogotá]] based club and racked up 28 appearances. His notable performances earned him the opportunity to represent his nation at the [[2011 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] hosted in [[Colombia]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kienyke.com/deportes/futbol/santiago-arias-y-el-sacrificio-para-ser-futbolista|title=Santiago Arias y el sacrificio para ser futbolista|access-date=1 September 2018|archive-date=2 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180902011916/https://www.kienyke.com/deportes/futbol/santiago-arias-y-el-sacrificio-para-ser-futbolista|url-status=dead}}</ref> After a successful spell at his club and internationally, he soon moved to Portugal to join the ranks of [[Lisbon]] team [[Sporting CP]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.colombia.com/futbol/noticias/sdi/13380/sporting-de-lisboa-presento-a-santiago-arias-su-mas-reciente-refuerzo|title = Sporting de Lisboa presentó a Santiago Arias, su más reciente refuerzo|date = 21 June 2011}}</ref>

=== Sporting CP ===
While representing the U20 national Colombian side in 2011, Arias attracted the scouts of Sporting CP. On 1 July 2011, Arias was ultimately signed by Sporting on a 5-year contract for a transfer free of €300,000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.elespectador.com/actualidad/santiago-arias-al-sporting-de-lisboa-276257/|title=ELESPECTADOR.COM|first=El|last=Espectador|date=9 June 2011|website=ELESPECTADOR.COM}}</ref> He made his debut in Portugal on 6 November replacing [[Matías Fernández (footballer, born 1986)|Matías Fernández]] in the 80th minute against [[U.D. Leiria]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/sporting-vs-uniao-leiria/241852|title = Portuguese Primeira Liga (Sky Sports)}}</ref> Despite making his first team debut, Arias spent most of his playing time with the [[Sporting Clube de Portugal B|B-Squad]] where he scored a goal in 28 appearances. He occasionally made appearances with the first squad, but never broke in for a permanent spot.

=== PSV ===
In early 2013, Arias was linked to the Dutch club PSV but nothing was finalized.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.abola.pt/nnh/ver.aspx?id=414669|title=abola.pt<!-- Bot generated title -->}}</ref> In July 2013, Arias was once again linked to the club where both parties agreed on finalizing a deal. It was then reported that Arias signed a four-year contract and PSV paid Sporting €1.6 million for a package deal including fellow Sporting teammate [[Stijn Schaars]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/es-co/news/4600/mercado-de-pases/2013/06/27/4078511/psv-tiene-en-la-mira-a-santiago-arias-otra-vez|title=PSV tiene en la mira a Santiago Arias otra vez &#124; Goal.com|website=www.goal.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.publico.pt/2013/07/13/desporto/noticia/psv-oficializa-schaars-por-tres-temporadas-1600148|title=PSV oficializa Stijn Schaars e Santiago Arias|website=PÚBLICO}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.futebol365.pt/noticias/artigo.asp?id=89179&cat=Sporting#.UeGLh420KSo|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130713172155/http://www.futebol365.pt/noticias/artigo.asp?id=89179&cat=Sporting%23.UeGLh420KSo|url-status=dead|archive-date=13 July 2013|title=Mercado: OFICIAL – Arias também já pertence aos quadros do PSV &#124; Notícias Sporting &#124; Futebol 365<!-- Bot generated title -->}}</ref> Upon his arrival, Arias was handed the number 13 shirt. He made his league debut on 3 August, playing a full 90 minutes in a 2–3 away win against [[ADO Den Haag]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nu.nl/sport/3542160/flitsend-half-uur-helpt-psv-langs-ado.html|title=Flitsend half uur helpt PSV langs ADO|date=3 August 2013|website=NU}}</ref> He made his first direct contribution for PSV as he scored the opening goal in a 3–2 home win over [[FC Twente]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.football-oranje.com/psv-eindhoven-3-2-twente-match-report/|title=PSV Eindhoven 3-2 Twente Match Report|date=8 February 2014|website=Football Oranje}}</ref> Arias made 25 league appearances for the [[2013–14 Eredivisie]] with PSV placing fourth thus earning a place in the [[2014–15 UEFA Europa League#Third qualifying round|2014–15 UEFA Europa League Third qualifying round]].

Arias appeared for the first time in a European competition in a match against [[SKN St. Pölten]] coming on as a second-half substitute in a match where PSV won 2-3.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/skn-st-polten-vs-psv/stats/323169|title=Europa League Qual (Sky Sports)|website=Sky Sports}}</ref> He then appeared in four group stage matches and played the first leg of the Round of 36 against [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg]]. Subsequent to an injury, Arias was ruled out of the second leg with his team being knocked out 4-0 on aggregate.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sin gravedad la lesión de Arias aseguró el club neerlandés {{!}} Goal.com|url=https://www.goal.com/es-co/news/5290/colombianos-en-resto-de-europa/2015/02/20/9129682/sin-gravedad-la-lesi%C3%B3n-de-arias|access-date=2021-12-18|website=www.goal.com}}</ref>

Despite an early exit from the [[Europa League]], PSV were crowned [[2014–15 Eredivisie]] thus making the conquest Arias's first European title. It was also the club's first title in eight years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sportskeeda.com/football/psv-eindhoven-win-22nd-dutch-eredivisie-title-three-games-spare|title=PSV Eindhoven win 22nd Dutch Eredivisie title with three games to spare|date=19 April 2015}}</ref>

In the 1–2 Champions League group stage loss against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern München]], Arias scored the opening goal with a header, which possibly came from an offside position.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/noblmd10-uefa-champions-league-psv-eindhoven-fc-bayern-muenchen-report-419154.jsp|title=Bayern into Last 16 as Lewandowski double downs PSV|website=bundesliga.com - the official Bundesliga website|access-date=17 April 2024|archive-date=12 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612162209/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/noblmd10-uefa-champions-league-psv-eindhoven-fc-bayern-muenchen-report-419154.jsp|url-status=dead}}</ref>

He played on 15 April 2018 as PSV beat rivals Ajax 3–0 to clinch the [[2017-18 Eredivisie|2017–18 Eredivisie]] title.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43776657|title=PSV Eindhoven 3-0 Ajax|work=BBC Sport}}</ref> The title would be Arias' 5th Dutch trophy in just 5 seasons within the Netherlands. Arias would then be named the [[Eredivisie Awards|Eredivisie Player of the Year]], having assisted 6 goals and scoring 3, as well as holding an 82% passing accuracy and winning 134 take ons.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eredivisie.nl/en-us/|title = Homepage}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|number=993837930085937152|user=EredivisieEN|title=Santiago Arias has been crowned as...|date=8 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|date=|title=Santiago Arias kroont zich tot speler van het seizoen 2017/2018 {{!}} Eredivisie|url=https://eredivisie.nl/nl-nl/uitgelicht/santiago-arias-kroont-zich-tot-speler-van-het-seizoen-20172018zoen-20172018|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180509221053/https://eredivisie.nl/nl-nl/uitgelicht/santiago-arias-kroont-zich-tot-speler-van-het-seizoen-20172018|archive-date=May 9, 2018|access-date=2021-12-18|website=eredivisie.nl}}</ref> He was also named in the league's best XI of the season.<ref>{{Cite web|date=|title=Elftal van het seizoen 2017/2018 bekend {{!}} Eredivisie|url=https://eredivisie.nl/en-us/uitgelicht/elftal-van-het-seizoen-20172018-bekend|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180511145808/https://eredivisie.nl/en-us/uitgelicht/elftal-van-het-seizoen-20172018-bekend|archive-date=May 11, 2018|access-date=2021-12-18|website=eredivisie.nl}}</ref>

===Atlético Madrid===
[[File:Santiago Arias 2019.jpg|thumb|150px|left|Arias during a match with [[Atlético Madrid]] in 2019]]
On 31 July 2018, it was announced that Arias completed a transfer to [[Atlético Madrid]] for a reported transfer fee of £11 million.<ref>[https://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/liga/2018-2019/atletico-madrid-sign-colombia-world-cup-defender-santiago-arias_sto6869598/story.shtml Atletico Madrid sign Colombia World Cup defender Santiago Arias] - [[Eurosport]]</ref> Upon his arrival, Arias was handed the number 4 shirt.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://colombia.as.com/colombia/2018/08/02/futbol/1533214036_339786.html|title=Atlético de Madrid le da el mítico '4' a Santiago Arias|date=2 August 2018}}</ref>

He made his unofficial debut in friendly against [[Cagliari Calcio|Cagliari]] replacing [[Juanfran (footballer, born 1985)|Juanfran]] at the start of the second half. Atlético went on to win the match with [[Borja Garcés]] scoring the sole goal.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://colombia.as.com/colombia/2018/08/08/futbol/1533757689_195028.html|title=Arias hace su estreno con el Atlético en amistoso ante Cagliari|date=8 August 2018}}</ref> He made his league debut for the club on 1 September, coming on as a substitute for [[José Giménez]] in a 2–0 defeat against [[Celta de Vigo]]. On 19 January 2019, he scored his first goal for ''Los Rojiblancos'' in a 0–3 defeat of [[SD Huesca]].

==== Loan to Bayer Leverkusen and Granada ====
On 24 September 2020, Arias joined [[Bayer Leverkusen]] on a season-long loan with an option to buy. A severe injury suffered in October while on international duty, however, cut his Leverkusen career short to a single [[Bundesliga]] appearance, sidelining him for the remainder of the season with a fractured fibula and damaged ligaments in his left ankle.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.beinsports.com/au/world-cup-qualifiers/news/arias-set-for-long-rehab-after-horror-ankle-s/1561406|title=Arias set for long rehab after horror ankle snap|publisher=beIN Sports|date=10 October 2020|access-date=28 August 2021}}</ref>

On 30 August 2021, Arias moved to [[Granada CF]] on a one-year loan deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.atleticodemadrid.com/noticias/acuerdo-con-el-granada-para-la-cesion-de-arias|title=Acuerdo con el Granada para la cesión de Arias|trans-title=Agreement with Granada for the loan of Arias|publisher=Atlético Madrid|language=es|date=30 August 2021|access-date=30 August 2021}}</ref> In December 2021, he suffered a hamstring injury, which required surgery, and was operated in January 2022 by surgeon Lasse Lempainen in [[Turku]], Finland.<ref>[https://www.iltalehti.fi/jalkapallo/a/b409fdae-f277-4169-802b-849a67f7ed15 ”Yksi hirveimmistä vammoista, mitä olen nähnyt” – kammoarvion saanut huippupelaaja leikattiin Turussa], [[Iltalehti]], 15 January 2022</ref>

=== FC Cincinnati ===
On 9 February 2023, Arias joined [[Major League Soccer]] club [[FC Cincinnati]] on a one‑year contract with an option for 2024, signing as a free agent after leaving [[Atlético Madrid]].<ref>https://www.fccincinnati.com/news/fc-cincinnati-sign-santiago-arias</ref> He made his MLS debut in the opening match of the 2023 season against [[Houston Dynamo]], though his initial run was disrupted by injury before he returned to regular first‑team action later in the campaign.<ref>https://global.espn.com/football/story/_/id/38514389/fc-cincinnati-wins-2023-mls-supporters-shield</ref>

Arias scored his first goal for Cincinnati on 21 June 2023 in a 3–0 home win against [[Toronto FC]], giving Cincinnati the lead in the 35th minute in a match that set a league record for the club’s most consecutive home victories in all competitions.<ref>https://ktvz.com/sports/ap-national-sports/2023/06/21/cincinnati-beats-toronto-3-0-for-record-13th-straight-home-win/</ref> Over the 2023 MLS season he made 32 appearances across all competitions, scoring three goals and providing two assists, contributing offensively as well as defensively from right‑back.

During his time with Cincinnati, Arias helped the club win the [[2023 Major League Soccer season|2023 Supporters’ Shield]], awarded to the team with the best regular‑season record in MLS.<ref>https://www.torontofc.ca/news/toronto-fc-2-fc-cincinnati-3-2023-mls-match-recap</ref>

=== Bahia ===
In January 2024, Arias signed with Brazilian [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[Esporte Clube Bahia|Bahia]] after leaving [[FC Cincinnati]] as a free agent following the expiration of his contract with the MLS side.<ref>https://ge.globo.com/google/amp/ba/futebol/times/bahia/noticia/2024/01/28/bahia-lembra-copa-do-mundo-e-anuncia-a-contratacao-do-lateral-direito-santiago-arias.ghtml</ref>

On 15 February 2024, Arias scored his first goal for Bahia in a 3–0 victory over [[América Futebol Clube (RN)|América‑RN]] in the [[Copa do Nordeste]].<ref>https://www.eluniversal.com.co/deportes/2025/03/10/gol-de-santiago-arias-en-victoria-de-bahia-y-finalista-del-campeonato-baiano</ref> During his time with the club, he made 73 official appearances, scored two goals and provided four assists, helping Bahia win the [[Campeonato Baiano]]. He also featured in the [[Copa Libertadores]] with Bahia. Arias left Bahia at the end of the 2025 season when his contract expired.<ref>https://www.bahianoticias.com.br/esportes/noticia/77256-ex-bahia-santiago-arias-e-o-novo-reforco-do-independiente-da-argentina_</ref>

=== Independiente ===
In January 2026, Arias signed with Argentine [[Argentine Primera División]] club [[Club Atlético Independiente|Independiente]] as a free agent after his spell at Bahia. He was officially presented by Independiente after completing his medical and signed a contract until December 2027.<ref>https://www.espn.com.pa/futbol/argentina/nota/_/id/16214479/santiago-arias-se-acerca-a-independiente-antes-del-mundial-2026?utm_</ref>

== International career ==
=== Youth ===
Arias was part of the [[Colombia national under-17 football team|Colombia U17]] team that finished fourth in the [[2009 FIFA U-17 World Cup]], playing all matches (except third place match, making a total of 6 appearances) and scoring the first penalty during the quarter-final penalty shoot-out against [[Turkey national under-17 football team|Turkey]].

In 2011, Arias played all 9 matches for the [[Colombia national under-20 football team|Colombia U-20]] team when they finished sixth in the [[2011 South American Youth Championship]]. [[Eduardo Lara]], Colombia's coach, also called him for the [[2011 Toulon Tournament]] where Arias, who started all 5 matches, was part of Colombia's team that won the final.

=== Senior ===
In September 2013, Arias received his first call up for Colombia's senior team to dispute the [[2014 World Cup]] qualifying matches against [[Chile national football team|Chile]] and [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]], following first choice [[Juan Camilo Zúñiga|Camilo Zúñiga]]'s injury.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://deportes.terra.com.co/futbol/pekerman-convoca-a-santiago-arias-por-el-lesionado-camilo-zuniga,5dc8f27e75f81410VgnCLD2000000dc6eb0aRCRD.html | title = Pekerman convoca a Santiago Arias por el lesionado Camilo Zúñiga | publisher = Terra Colombia | access-date = 6 October 2013 | archive-date = 13 August 2016 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160813174121/https://deportes.terra.com.co/futbol/pekerman-convoca-a-santiago-arias-por-el-lesionado-camilo-zuniga,5dc8f27e75f81410VgnCLD2000000dc6eb0aRCRD.html | url-status = dead }}</ref> He made his debut against [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay]] and played the entire match in a 1–2 away victory at [[Asunción]].

Arias was included in [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]]'s 23-man squad for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]] in Brazil. He made three appearances in the tournament, coming on as a substitute in all of Colombia's group stage matches. The following year, Arias was included in the final squad for the [[2015 Copa America]]. He appeared twice at the tournament, including the quarter-final 0–0 draw against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] where Colombia were eliminated 5–4 on penalties.

He was a part of the Colombian squad that finished third place at the [[Copa América Centenario]].

Arias was selected in [[José Pékerman]]'s 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - Final 23-man lists &#124; Goal.com|website=www.goal.com}}</ref> He started in all four of Colombia's matches as his nation was eliminated in the Round of 16 against [[England national football team|England]].

